It all began with Lockdown Level 5. The pandemic had a global impact and two years on there’s still no end in sight. Here's a look back at a time in history we won't easily forget. eNCA's Gcina Mvana reports. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - When President Cyril Ramaphosa announced the country's response to the COVID-19 pandemic in 2020, restrictions were expected to last for 21 days. This turned into weeks, and then months and then years. READ: SA Lockdown | Calls to scrap COVID-19 regulations The 26th of March marks two years since the first lockdown. At first dismissed as nothing more than bad flu, COVID-19 has become a global pandemic. WATCH | COVID-19 | Dr Aslam Dasoo reacts to Ramaphosa's address The virus wreaked havoc, crippling economies, isolating people and closed borders. Here's a look back at a time in history we won't easily forget. * eNCA's Gcina Mvana reports.